<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Rayne on 05-31-2002 10:42 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Thanks to those who gave congrats, but that really wasn't the point =).

In a game that requires extremely rare drops for some classes(many including Wizards, Mages, and SKs) and trips to the 7th Isle of Air (mages), requires relatively difficult or heavily competed for items for others (Warrior, Bard) and some that are extremely contested (Clerics!) why in hell do Rogues get such a cakewalk?!?  Wasn't it enough that my Rogue at 46 and a mediocre weapon (some dagger dropped by Deathfang in Chardok) could outdamage my 60 SK with 20+ AA and a quest weapon (Greenmist) that took a three+ days /played and a full group for multiple drops?  No, let me put in 10 hours (including General fights) and walk away with a 15 damage piercer with 40% haste, +40 attack (it makes a difference, Rogues really watch attack rating), and a slew of stats while I've killed Phinny over 10 times without getting a Wizard or Mage piece, Jumpy over 20 times without getting the stupid powder, etc.

I don't want all the Epics to be screwed up like Wizards and Mages, I want all epics to be closer to the Rogues.  Yea, it pisses me off if you couldn't tell =P.  I tell my friends that it's just easier to work within the gaming system (hence our three new Rogue twinks), but it's still depressing for those of us who loved our ORIGINAL characters.

Oh well, if you decide you want an epic all you have to do is roll up a Rogue twink on a separate account and 5 days /played later you too can have an epic, just not necessarily the one you want =/.

Rayne</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
